##There's a little bit of movement in the air

WECHAT denganqing1984

Feature description, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After many days of cloudy and rainy weather, on the third day of the Lunar New Year, it began to become cloudy. The concrete road in the dyke was blown dry by the wind, and there was a slight loosening in the air. You can almost feel the stern situation of the locked doors of every family on the 1st and 2nd Day of the 1st Year of the 1st Year of the 20th Year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th year of the 20th century becoming relaxed, the mask is pulled under the lip.

After two days of being cooped up at home, my father went out to read the notice on the wall near the entrance to the polder. I happened to see it on the second floor and immediately ran to the balcony to tell him to hurry back. "It's all right, " he said, "I'll just look. " I insisted that he hurry back, and he reluctantly turned back. "where's your mask? " He said. "It's in my pocket. " I said, unkindly. "PUT IT on now! "

When I went down to the kitchen for dinner, there was a big bucket of laundry on the stairs, and I carried it up to the second floor to dry it and came down again. Mother was cooking, so she had gone to do some washing. I asked her if she was wearing a mask, and she said yes. My mother told me that she met Kikuyoshi when she was washing clothes in the pond.

Kikuyoshi invited my mother to go to the Temple to Worship Incense. My mother said it was too serious to go now, kikuyoshi said angrily, "it's all a rumor! Don't believe such nonsense!"The mother replied to her:"Where is the rumor? You didn't watch TV, the Central Committee said it was so serious that people should not go out in the house,"said Kikuyoshi. It's all such a crazy thing. I can't get through the year, and I can't worship incense. That's not a thing."after Kikuyoshi left, another laundry aunt said: "They are busy in the hospital, do not know how hard. She closed in the House for two days, so the chatter. "

Two days. It's only the first two days. Everyone can still be in the room. On the third day, the grim situation was softened by the illusion that the country was safe. One after another, people opened the door, and began to have children playing in the house chase, there are uncles on the cement road, while smoking and talking to people. It's okay. It's okay. You don't have to scare your own family. They all have it in them. I mean, there's no one around to get it. I mean, I've never heard of anyone I knew dying.

Even my father watched TV at home for two days. When I wasn't paying attention, he went out to the Mahjong Parlor in the dike to see the cards. He didn't come back until lunch, i said to him seriously, "GRANDPA, you can't run around like this. You should be responsible not only for your own family, but also for the whole family. " He replied, "Oh, it's all right. They're all from our own land, so who's infecting them? " I said, he's getting impatient.

I began to realize that there was a sense of resignation in my father. He felt that in the face of such a disaster, you infected is your bad luck, no infection then do not frighten yourself. It's fate, anyway. If it comes down to you, there's no point in you running. As for the admonition to wear a mask and wash your hands frequently, it seems to him that it is both troublesome and useless, and that he can not do the tedious work of prevention.

Perhaps not only my father, those uncles, aunts have such a thought, and then further investigation is in the fate of the powerless before it. As for my warning of "jumping up and down" , they see it as a sign of childishness and don't take it to heart.

The TV reports of the epidemic, they have seen the numbness. In the final analysis, they felt that this was far away from them. Although the city was sealed off and people everywhere seemed to be in a state of panic, it was still so peaceful inside the dyke. The epidemic doesn't know what the future holds, but it's impossible to keep them locked up in their homes for so long. At this point, the epidemic became their talk, rather than a frightening invisible monster, after all, it has not yet come, after all, there is no bloody reality in front of them.
